ty Perry\n* [[Dr. Luke|Lukasz Gottwald]]\n* [[Max Martin]]}}\n| producer   = Cameron Mizell\n| prev_title =\n| prev_year  =\n| next_title = [&] Delinquents\n| next_year  = 2011\n}}\n\n[[Atlanta]]-based [[metalcore]] band, [[Woe, Is Me]] covered the track for the [[compilation album]] ''[[Punk Goes Pop Volume 03.]]'', which was released on November 2, 2010. The song was leaked on October 6, 2010, and was officially released as a single for digital download on October 21, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=Punk Goes Pop, Vol. 3 |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/punk-goes-pop-vol.-3/id395852661 |publisher=iTunes Store |accessdate=11 April 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140228210235/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/punk-goes-pop-vol.-3/id395852661 |archivedate=28 February 2014 }}</ref> [[MTV News]] described the band's cover as \"50 percent faithful to the original and..... 50 percent punishing, metal and gravel-throated growls. It must be heard to be believed.\"<ref>{{cite news|last=Ryan|first=Chris|title=Video: Woe, Is Me on their Pop Goes Punk cover of Katy Perry's \"Hot n Cold\"|url=http://buzzworthy.mtv.com/2010/11/10/video-woe-is-me-katy-perry-hot-n-cold/|publisher=MTV News|accessdate=April 11, 2014}}</ref>\n\n===The Baseballs version===\n\"Hot n Cold\" was covered by the German [[rockabilly]] cover band [[The Baseballs]] in 2009 from their debut album ''[[Strike! (album)|Strike!]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Strike! - The Baseballs|url=http://www.allmusic.com/album/strike%21-mw0001745954|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=January 14, 2014}}</ref> Their cover charted in the band's home country of Germany, as well as in Finland and Switzerland.\n\n====Charts====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Chart (2010)\n! Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|68|artist=The Baseballs|song=Hot n Cold|songid=582727|accessdate=May 29, 2019}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Finland|7|artist=The Baseballs|song=Hot n Cold}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Switzerland|52|artist=The Baseballs|song=Hot n Cold}}\n|}\n\n===Other cover versions===\n* The song was covered by British [[ska]] and [[Independent music|indie]] band [[Kid British]] on their 2009 [[Extended play|EP]] ''iTunes Live: London Festival '09''.<ref name=\"EP\">{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?id=324015923&s=143444|title=iTunes Live: London Festival '09 \u2013 EP|publisher=iTunes Store|accessdate=July 15, 2009}} Note: Need iTunes to view link</ref>\n* [[Selena Gomez & the Scene]] performed the song during their 2009 [[Selena Gomez & the Scene: Live in Concert]] tour.<ref>{{cite web|last=Daw|first=Robbie|title=Watch Selena Gomez Cover Backstreet Boys and Katy Perry Live|url=http://www.idolator.com/5406262/watch-selena-gomez-covers-backstreet-boys-and-katy-perry-live|publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|accessdate=January 14, 2014}}</ref>\n\n{{Clear}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Romanian Top 100 number ones of the 2000s]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|katy-perry|hot-n-cold}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Katy Perry}}\n{{Woe, Is Me}}\n\n[[Category:2008 singles]]\n[[Category:Katy Perry songs]]\n[[Category:Billboard Adult Top 40 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Austria]]\n[[Category:Canadian Hot 100 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Denmark]]\n[[Category:European Hot 100 Singles number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Finland]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Germany]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Hungary]]\n[[Category:Dutch Top 40 number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Norway]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Poland]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Romania]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Number-one singles in Turkey]]\n[[Category:Record Report Pop Rock General number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Max Martin]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Katy Perry]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Dr. Luke]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Dr. Luke]]\n[[Category:Billboard Mainstream Top 40 (Pop Songs) number-one singles]]\n[[Category:Woe, Is Me songs]]\n[[Category:Dance-pop songs]]\n[[Category:2008 songs]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2008 single by Katy Perry}}\n{{good article}}\n{{Infobox song\n| name       = Hot n Cold\n| cover      = Hot N Cold (Official Single Cover) by Katy Perry.png\n| alt        =\n| border     = yes\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Katy Perry]]\n| album      = [[One of the Boys (Katy Perry album)|One of the Boys]]\n| released   = {{start date|2008|09|09}}\n| format     = {{flatlist|\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[CD single]]\n}}\n| recorded   = December 2007\n| studio     = Dr. Luke's Studios, Legacy Recording Studio ([[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], US)<br />Conway Recording Studio ([[Hollywood]], [[California]], US)\n| venue      =\n| genre      = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[dance-pop]]\n}}\n| length     = {{duration|m=3|s=40}}\n| label      = [[Capitol Records|Capitol]]\n| writer     = {{flatlist|\n* Katy Perry\n* [[Dr. Luke|Lukasz Gottwald]]\n* [[Max Martin]]\n}}\n| producer   = {{flatlist|\n* [[Dr. Luke]]\n* [[Benny Blanco]]\n}}\n| prev_title = [[I Kissed a Girl]]\n| prev_year  = 2008\n| next_title = [[Thinking of You (Katy Perry song)|Thinking of You]]\n| next_year  = 2009\n| misc       = {{external music video|{{YouTube|kTHNpusq654|\"Hot n Cold\"}}}}\n}}\n\"'''Hot n Cold'''\" is a song by American singer [[Katy Perry]]. The song was written by Perry, [[Dr. Luke]], and [[Max Martin]] and produced by Dr. Luke and [[Benny Blanco]] for her second studio album, ''[[One of the Boys (Katy Perry album)|One of the Boys]]'' (2008). The track was released as the album's second single on September 9, 2008. The lyrics address an unstable romantic relationship caused by a partner's [[mood swing]]s.\n\nThe song reached number three on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]], becoming Perry's second consecutive top three single, following \"[[I Kissed a Girl]]\". It also became Perry's second top five single in the United Kingdom, Australia, Ireland and New Zealand, and topped the charts in Finland, Germany, Canada, Norway, Spain, and Denmark, among others. To date, \"Hot n Cold\" has sold over 5.7 million copies in the US, making it one of Perry's highest-selling singles in the nation.\n\nTo promote \"Hot n Cold\", Perry marked the song's live debut with a performance on [[NBC]]'s ''[[Today (American TV program)|Today]]''. She also performed the song at the [[2008 MTV Europe Music Awards]], which she hosted. The song's music video, which was directed by [[Alan Ferguson (director)|Alan Ferguson]], was released on October 1, 2008, and features Perry as a bride who is about to get married to her fianc\u00e9, who experiences a daydream in which she pursues him after he flees from the wedding. \"Hot n Cold\" was nominated for the [[Grammy Award]] for [[Grammy Award for Best Female Pop Vocal Performance|Best Female Pop Vocal Performance]] at the [[52nd Annual Grammy Awards]]. Perry also performed the song on the [[Hello Katy Tour]], [[California Dreams Tour]], [[The Prismatic World Tour|Prismatic World Tour]] and [[Witness: The Tour]].\n\n==Background and composition==\n\n\"Hot n Cold\" was written by Perry, Dr. Luke and Max Martin and produced by Dr. Luke and [[Benny Blanco]]. It was recorded in December 2007 in three studios: Dr. Luke's Studios in [[New York City]], Conway Recording Studio in [[Hollywood]], [[California]], and Legacy Recording Studios in [[New York City]]. It was mixed in MixStar Studios in [[Virginia Beach, Virginia|Virginia Beach]].<ref name=OOTBnotes>{{cite AV media notes |title=One of the Boys |titlelink=One of the Boys (Katy Perry album) |others=[[Katy Perry]] |year=2008 |type=liner notes |publisher=[[Capitol Records]] |location=[[United States]]}}</ref> The collaboration between Perry and Dr. Luke was set up by record executives at [[Capitol Records]], who felt that ''One of the Boys'' was lacking an \"undeniable smash or two\" at the time, and the two co-wrote \"I Kissed a Girl\" and \"Hot n Cold\" as a result.<ref>{{cite web|title=Interview with Chris Anokute|url=http://www.hitquarters.com/index.php3?page=intrview/opar/intrview_AnokuteCorrection.html|publisher=HitQuarters|accessdate=21 March 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140713071228/http://www.hitquarters.com/index.php3?page=intrview%2Fopar%2Fintrview_AnokuteCorrection.html|archive-date=13 July 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Perry revealed that the song was originally considered for release as the album's first single, before \"I Kissed a Girl\" was chosen.<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry Exclusive Interview|url=http://www.thestarscoop.com/music/katy-perry-exclusive-interview/|publisher=The Star Scoop|accessdate=4 January 2014}}</ref>\n\nWritten in the key of [[G major]],<ref name=MusicNotes /> \"Hot n Cold\" is a [[Pop music|pop]] and [[dance-pop]] song which utilizes [[guitars]] and [[synthesizers]].<ref name=DigitalSpy /><ref name=musicomh /><ref name=\"CA\">{{cite web|title= Katy Perry \u2014 One Of The Boys |date= July 8, 2008 |work= [[ChartAttack]] |url= http://www.chartattack.com/news/2008/07/08/katy-perry/ |accessdate= June 19, 2015}}</ref> It has a length of three minutes and forty seconds (3:40),<ref>{{cite web|title=iTunes \u2013 Music \u2013 One of the Boys by Katy Perry|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/one-of-the-boys/id715891425|publisher=[[iTunes Store]]|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref> and runs at a moderately fast [[tempo]] of 132 [[beats per minute]].<ref name=MusicNotes>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry 'Hot n Cold' Sheet Music|url=http://www.musicnotes.com/sheetmusic/mtdFPE.asp?ppn=MN0067923&|publisher=MusicNotes|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref> The lyrics of the song address a lover of Perry whose [[mood swing]]s are affecting the couple's relationship. The song opens with Perry confronting her former partner over his frequent changes of mind, singing \"You change your mind like a girl changes clothes / Yeah you [[Premenstrual syndrome|PMS]] like a bitch\". In the chorus, she uses [[Opposite (semantics)|antonyms]] to describe her partner's mood changes, with the chorus of the song including the lines \"You're hot then you're cold / You're yes then you're no / You're in then you're out / You're up then you're down\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Hohman|first=Charles A.|title=Katy Perry: One of the Boys|url=http://www.popmatters.com/review/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys/|work=PopMatters|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\nAlex Fletcher of [[Digital Spy]] gave the song 3 out of 5 stars, saying \"this track doesn't live up to the hype surrounding its singer, but the choppy guitars and whooshing synths have a certain charm.\"<ref name=DigitalSpy>{{cite web|last=Fletcher|first=Alex|title=Katy Perry: 'Hot n Cold' Music Review|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/music/review/a133632/katy-perry-hot-n-cold.html|work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=4 January 2014}}</ref> In his review for [[MusicOMH]], Darren Harvey called \"Hot n Cold\" a \"[[Tiffany (American singer)|Tiffany]]-style '80s pop number\".<ref name=musicomh>{{cite web|last=Harvey|first=Darren|title=Katy Perry \u2013 One of the Boys|url=http://www.musicomh.com/reviews/albums/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys|publisher=[[MusicOMH]]|accessdate=4 January 2014}}</ref> ''[[ChartAttack]]'' noted the \"frenetic [[dance-pop]]\" of the track.<ref name=\"CA\" /> In a less positive review, Sal Cinquemani from ''[[Slant Magazine]]'' criticized the song, saying \"Perry confuses political incorrectness with being subversive on tracks like \"Hot n Cold,\" in which she, in the process of skewering guys who change their minds 'like girls change clothes,' just winds up sounding mildly sexist.\"<ref name=Slant>{{cite web|last=Cinquemani|first=Sal|title=Katy Perry: One of the Boys|url=http://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/katy-perry-one-of-the-boys|work=[[Slant Magazine]]|accessdate=4 January 2014}}</ref> Jon Caramanica of ''[[The New York Times]]'' compared the song to \"[[U + Ur Hand]]\" by [[Pink (singer)|Pink]], which was also produced by Dr. Luke, saying that it does not share the latter's \"passion\".<ref>{{cite news|last=Caramanica|first=Jon|title=Critics' Choice \u2013 New CDs from the Hold Steady, Plies, Katy Perry, Guillermo Klein and Bonnie (Prince) Billy|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/06/16/arts/music/16choi.html?_r=0|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=4 January 2014}}</ref> Lizzie Ennever of [[BBC]] felt the track was not \"the most single-worthy song\".<ref>{{cite web|last=Ennever|first=Lizzie|title=Katy Perry One Of The Boys Review|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/dv25|accessdate=May 19, 2014|publisher=[[BBC]]|year=2008}}</ref> ''[[The Guardian]]'' wrote that the song \"didn't seem to capture the public's imagination\" the way her previous single \"I Kissed a Girl\" did.<ref>{{cite news|title=Katy Perry gets a Ukrainian makeover|url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/musicblog/2009/mar/26/katy-perry-ukrainian-makeover|accessdate=September 15, 2014|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=March 26, 2009}}</ref> The song was nominated for the [[Grammy Award for Best Female Pop Vocal Performance]] at the [[52nd Annual Grammy Awards]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Complete List of Nominees for the 52nd Annual Grammy Awards|url=http://eonline.com/news/156188/complete-list-of-nominees-for-the-52nd-annual-grammy-awards|publisher=[[E!]]. [[NBCUniversal]]|accessdate=4 January 2014}}</ref> but lost to [[Beyonc\u00e9]]'s \"[[Halo (Beyonc\u00e9 song)|Halo]]\".<ref>{{cite web|title=52nd Annual Grammy Awards winners: A complete list|url=http://www.hitfix.com/articles/52-annual-grammy-awards-winners-a-complete-list|publisher=[[HitFix]]|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Chart performance==\n[[File:Katy Perry at Madison Square Garden (36757922824).jpg|thumb|Perry performing \"Hot n Cold\" during [[Witness: The Tour]] in [[Madison Square Garden]]]]\n\"Hot n Cold\" debuted on the US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] at number 88 on June 28, 2008, due to strong digital downloads after the album's release, falling off the chart the next week. It re-entered the Hot 100 on August 23, again at number 88. The song peaked at number three on the Hot 100 on November 22, making it her second top-three hit after \"I Kissed a Girl\". \"Hot n Cold\" was in the top ten for 18 weeks, spending more time in the top ten than Perry's previous single \"I Kissed a Girl\", which spent 14 weeks. The song was also a bigger radio hit than \"I Kissed a Girl\", becoming Perry's first number one on both US [[Mainstream Top 40 (Pop Songs)|Mainstream Top 40]] and [[Adult Top 40]] radio charts. It remained in the Hot 100 for a total of 39 weeks.<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry \u2013 Chart history|url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/305595/katy-perry/chart?page=1&f=379|work=Billboard|accessdate=9 April 2014}}</ref> As of 2017, \"Hot n Cold\" has sold 5.7 million copies in the United States, making it Perry's sixth best-selling single in the country.<ref name=us_sales>{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6450846/ask-billboard-controversial-hits-katy-perrys-sales-taylor-swifts?page=0%2C1 |title=Ask Billboard: Controversial Hits, Katy Perry's Sales & Taylor Swift's Radio Reign |last=Trust |first=Gary |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |date=January 25, 2015 |accessdate=January 25, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn Canada, the song debuted at number 73 and reached the number one position on the chart on November 20. It was later certified six-times-platinum.<ref>{{cite certification|region=Canada|type=single|title=Hot N Cold|artist=Katy Perry|certyear=2010|relyear=2008}}</ref> The song peaked at number four on the [[UK Singles Chart]] on December 7, and was certified platinum.<ref>{{cite certification|region=United Kingdom|type=single|title=Hot N Cold|artist=Katy Perry|certyear=2009|relyear=2008}}</ref> In Ireland, the song peaked at number three. \"Hot n Cold\" debuted on the [[Media Control Charts|German Singles Chart]] at number two due to strong digital download sales, before topping the chart and spending eight consecutive weeks at number one in Germany.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://acharts.us/song/36447 |title=Katy Perry \u2013 Hot n Cold \u2013 Music Charts |publisher=\u03b1Charts.us |accessdate=2010-12-02}}</ref> In Australia, the single debuted in the top 50, before reaching its peak at number four. It has since been certified five-times-platinum in the country.<ref>{{cite certification|region=Australia|type=single|title=Hot N Cold|artist=Katy Perry|certyear=2009|relyear=2008}}</ref> The song peaked at number one in the Czech Republic, and spent ten consecutive weeks at the top of the chart.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ifpicr.cz/hitparada/index.php?a=titul&hitparada=2&titul=146361&sec=f61ccff25cd04edd4b93eda3258cc4f3 |title=\u010cns Ifpi |publisher=Ifpicr.cz |accessdate=2010-12-02}}</ref> \"Hot n Cold\" reached the number one position in Denmark, later being certified two-times-platinum,<ref>{{cite certification|region=Denmark|type=single|title=Hot N Cold|artist=Katy Perry|certyear=2009|relyear=2008}}</ref> and hit number one in Austria before being certified platinum.<ref>{{cite certification|region=Austria|type=single|title=Hot N Cold|artist=Katy Perry|certyear=2009|relyear=2008}}</ref>\n\n==Music video==\n[[File:Hot n Cold video.png|thumb|left|Perry corners Alexander leading a zebra on a leash, before he awakens from his daydream.]]\nThe video begins with Perry at a wedding, about to exchange vows with her diffident fianc\u00e9 Alexander (played by actor/model Alexander Francis Rodriguez). Perry says her vows, but Alexander hesitates and the church anxiously waits for him to say \"I do\". Perry appears frustrated and the music begins to play, with the congregation dancing as disco lights flash. Perry begins to sing the song to Alexander before he flees the altar. She pursues him, and they proceed to play a [[Cat and mouse|cat-and-mouse game]]. Perry corners him in a warehouse, and Alexander is pulled into an audience and forced to crowd-surf while watching Perry perform the song on stage. He manages to escape but walks out to find Perry in her wedding dress surrounded by several other brides carrying baseball bats. Perry confronts him, but he is able to get away.\n\nPerry and the other brides chase after him. When Alexander pulls out his phone, Perry is on the screen singing to him. He flees the warehouse and finds Perry outside wearing [[Hip hop fashion|urban clothing]], surrounded by dancers dressed similarly. When he turns around, he discovers that he has been cornered by Perry and the group of angry brides. He stumbles and the dancers surround him as he lies on the ground, before Perry approaches him leading a zebra on a leash. Alexander blinks and finds himself back at the altar in the church, revealing that the previous events were just his fantasy. The priest asks him again if he accepts his vows, and this time he says \"I do\". The crowd in the church breaks out into cheers and sighs of relief as Perry runs victoriously down the aisle with him.\n\nPerry's friend [[Jadyn Maria]] appears in the music video as a bridesmaid, and her parents Keith and Mary Hudson also make cameos.<ref>{{cite web|title=\"All Access:\" Katy Perry|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/all-access-katy-perry/|publisher=[[CBS News]]|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Edelstein|first=Paula|title=Jadyn Maria Interview \u2013 Recording and Touring with Ne-Yo|url=http://www.singeruniverse.com/jadynmaria123.htm|publisher=Singer Universe|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref> The video for \"Hot n Cold\" was recorded in Los Angeles in September 2008 and released on October 1, 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.musicvideocast.com/katy-perry-hot-n-cold.html|publisher=Music Video Cast|accessdate=September 15, 2014|title=Katy Perry \u2013 Hot N Cold (Music Video)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140916124755/http://www.musicvideocast.com/katy-perry-hot-n-cold.html|archive-date=September 16, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> It was directed by [[Alan Ferguson (director)|Alan Ferguson]]. ''Rolling Stone'' described the music video as \"a colorful cat-and-mouse chase that's equal parts goofy and glam.\"<ref>{{cite web|title=The Complete Guide to Katy Perry's Music Videos|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/pictures/the-complete-guide-to-katy-perrys-music-videos-20110622/hot-n-cold-2008-0914113|work=Rolling Stone|accessdate=11 April 2014}}</ref> Capital FM wrote that the video \"had us in stitches\".<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry \u2013 Hot N Cold|url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/katy-perry/videos/katy-perry-hot-n-cold/|publisher=Capital FM|accessdate=September 15, 2014|date=October 13, 2008}}</ref>\n\nThe music video on YouTube has over 950 million views as of March 2020.<ref>{{Citation|last=KatyPerryVEVO|title=Katy Perry - Hot N Cold (Official)|date=2008-10-13|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kTHNpusq654|accessdate=2017-06-03}}</ref>\n\n==Live performances==\n[[File:Katy Perry - The Prismatic World Tour Chile (23291946549).jpg|thumb|Perry performing \"Hot n Cold\" during Prismatic World Tour.]]\nPerry made the live television premiere performance of \"Hot n Cold\" on [[NBC]]'s ''[[Today (American TV program)|Today]]'' on August 29, 2008.<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry Gets Lucky Performing on the Today Show|url=http://neonlimelight.com/2009/07/25/katy-perry-gets-lucky-performing-on-the-today-show/|publisher=Neon Limelight|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref> Perry performed the song live at the [[2008 MTV Europe Music Awards]] in [[Liverpool]], which she also hosted, on November 6 to close the show.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Paine|first=Andre|title=American Acts Win Big at MTV EMAs|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/1043562/american-acts-win-big-at-mtv-emas|magazine=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref> The song was also performed as the opener at the 2008 [[YouTube Live]] event on November 22, 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2013/11/1/5052440/youtube-live-a-disastrous-spectacle-google-would-like-you-to-forget |title=YouTube Live: a disastrous spectacle Google would like you to forget |publisher=[[The Verge]] |accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref> Perry performed the song with [[Taylor Swift]] at the [[Staples Center]] show during the [[Fearless Tour]] on April 15, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|last=Adickman|first=Erika Brooks|title=Taylor Swift Sings 'Hot n Cold' with Katy Perry, Proves She Can Share a Spotlight|url=http://www.idolator.com/5478172/taylor-swift-sings-hot-n-cold-with-katy-perry-proves-she-can-share-a-spotlight|publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]. [[Spin Media]]|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref> The song has been included in the setlists of Perry's [[Hello Katy Tour|Hello Katy]], [[California Dreams Tour|California Dreams]], and [[The Prismatic World Tour|Prismatic World]] [[concert#concert tours|tours]]. During the California Dreams Tour, Perry performed a \"magic trick\" that involved her changing into 7 different outfits during the number.<ref>{{cite news|last=Pareles|first=Jon|title=Katy Perry's Sweetened Raunch at Nassau Coliseum|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/06/20/arts/music/katy-perrys-sweetened-raunch-at-nassau-coliseum-review.html?_r=2&|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|publisher=[[Arthur Ochs Sulzberger, Jr.]]|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref> Perry performed the song on her [[The Prismatic World Tour]] in a slow jazz version with her dressing in a pink-catsuit with her dancers dressed in a similar way.<ref>{{cite news|last=Wyatt|first=Daisy|title=Katy Perry's Prismatic World Tour, The O2, review|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/reviews/katy-perrys-prismatic-world-tour-the-o2-review-pop-princess-fails-to-take-flight-9444074.html|newspaper=[[The Independent]]|publisher=Independent Print Limited|accessdate=30 May 2014}}</ref> It is also part of the setlist of Perry's [[Witness: The Tour]] in a medley with \"[[Last Friday Night (T.G.I.F.)|Last Friday Night (T.G.I.F)]]\", a song from her album [[Teenage Dream (Katy Perry album)|''Teenage Dream'']].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.azcentral.com/story/entertainment/music/2018/01/20/katy-perry-concert-review-phoenix-glendale-witness-tour/1032740001/|title=Katy Perry show bears witness to singer's enduring appeal a decade after 'Kissed a Girl'|author=Ed Masley|date=January 20, 2018|accessdate=January 22, 2018|work=[[The Arizona Republic|AZ Central]]}}</ref>\n\n==Usage in media==\n* Perry filmed a performance of a version of the song with puppet character [[Elmo]] from ''[[Sesame Street]]'', which was intended to teach children about antonyms. The clip was originally scheduled to run on the 41st-season premiere of the educational children's program on September 27, 2010, however the performance, which was uploaded to [[YouTube]] earlier, garnered controversy over the amount of [[cleavage (breasts)|cleavage]] Perry had on display in the video. Before the scheduled airing, [[Sesame Workshop]] announced that after controversy over the clip, \"We have decided we will not air the segment on the television broadcast of ''Sesame Street'', which is aimed at preschoolers. Katy Perry fans will still be able to view the video on YouTube.\"<ref>{{cite news|title=Katy Perry Too Hot for 'Sesame Street'?|url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/katy-perry-too-hot-for-sesame-street/|publisher=CBS News|date=September 23, 2010|accessdate=January 14, 2014}}</ref> Perry mocked the controversy shortly afterwards in a skit during her appearance on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]'' as a musical guest, wearing an Elmo-themed shirt which showed large amounts of cleavage.<ref>{{cite web|title=Katy Perry mocks Sesame Street ban|url=http://www.capitalfm.com/artists/katy-perry/videos/hot-n-cold-sesame-street/|publisher=Capital FM|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref>\n* The song was used as the theme music for ''[[MasterChef Australia]]'' and its associated TV ads.<ref>{{cite web|last=Griffin|first=Michelle|title=Junior MasterChef recap: The only loser? Katy Perry|url=http://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/tv-and-radio/junior-masterchef-recap-the-only-loser-katy-perry-20100913-1590h.html|work=[[The Sydney Morning Herald]]|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref>\n* \"Hot n Cold\" was featured in the opening sequence for the film ''[[The Ugly Truth (film)|The Ugly Truth]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Ugly Truth|url=http://nypress.com/the-ugly-truth/|publisher=[[New York Press]]|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref>\n* The song was featured in the trailer for the film ''[[The Proposal (2009 film)|The Proposal]]''<ref>{{cite web|title=The Proposal 2009 Soundtrack|url=http://www.theost.com/2009/the_proposal.html|publisher=TheOST|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref> and the final trailer for ''[[Inside Out (2015 film)|Inside Out]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=INSIDE OUT \u2013 Official Final Trailer (2015) Disney Pixar Animated Movie HD|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7ZLOYXKmIkw|publisher=CBR Trailers|via=YouTube|accessdate=13 June 2015}}</ref>\n* It is featured in the 2013 Brazilian film ''[[Meu Passado Me Condena]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3034258/soundtrack?ref_=tt_ql_trv_7|title=Meu Passado Me Condena: O Filme (2013) - Soundtracks|publisher=[[IMDb]]|accessdate=2018-02-04}}</ref>''\n* Perry recorded a cover version in the fictional language of \"[[Simlish]]\" which was used in the [[video game]] ''[[The Sims 2]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Parrish|first=Kevin|title=Katy Perry Does Video in \"Simlish\"|url=http://www.tomsguide.com/us/sims-katy-perry-kissed-girl,news-2645.html|publisher=[[Tom's Hardware|Tom's Guide]]|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref>\n* The song appeared in the second ''[[iCarly]]'' soundtrack, ''[[iSoundtrack II]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Vena|first=Jocelyn|title=Miranda Cosgrove Drops Second 'iCarly' Soundtrack|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1677772/miranda-cosgrove-icarly-isoundtrack-ii.jhtml|publisher=[[MTV News]]|accessdate=14 January 2014}}</ref>\n* During the 2010 [[Saint George's Day|Sant Jordi]] festivities in [[Barcelona]], the (350+) staff in one of the main buildings of the [[Polytechnic University of Catalonia]]  performed a notorious [[lip dub]] of the song that reached over 150,000 views on YouTube.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5wNbaFB_4OQ|title=LipdUPC|first=|last=lipdUPC|date=7 May 2010|publisher=|accessdate=31 October 2016|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n* This song was used in 2009 on the  [[WIND Hellas]] commercials for the f2g pre-paid card 1 year free calls.\n<ref> {{cite\nweb|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ql8dQ9b9VFM\n</ref>\n<!--Do NOT add additional entries without citations per [[WP:Verifiability]] and [[WP:No original research]]-->\n\n==Track listing==\n; CD Single<ref>https://www.discogs.com/Katy-Perry-Hot-N-Cold-Remixes/release/1835631</ref>\n# \"Hot n Cold (Album Version)\" \u2013 3:40\n# \"Hot n Cold (Instrumental)\" \u2013 3:40\n# \"Hot n Cold (A Cappella)\" \u2013 3:34\n# \"Hot n Cold (Rock Mix)\" \u2013 3:41\n# \"Hot n Cold (Innerpartysystem Remix)\" \u2013 4:40\n# \"Hot n Cold (Bimbo Jones Radio Edit)\" \u2013 3:50\n# \"Hot n Cold (Manhattan Clique Radio Edit)\" \u2013 3:54\n# \"Hot n Cold (Jason Nevins Radio Edit)\" \u2013 3:57\n\n==Remixes==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n;[[Almighty Records|Almighty]] Mixes<ref>https://www.discogs.com/Katy-Perry-vs-Almighty-Cover-Girlz-Hot-N-Cold/release/1434557</ref>\n* \"Hot n Cold (Almighty 12\" Anthem Mix)\" \u2013 8:00\n* \"Hot n Cold (Almighty 12\" Anthem Instrumental)\" \u2013 8:00\n* \"Hot n Cold (Almighty 12\" Anthem Dub)\" \u2013 7:14\n* \"Hot n Cold (Almighty Anthem Radio Edit)\" \u2013 4:01\n; Bimbo Jones Mixes<ref>https://www.discogs.com/Katy-Perry-Hot-N-Cold/release/1843578</ref>\n* \"Hot n Cold (Bimbo Jones Club Mix)\" \u2013 8:02\n* \"Hot n Cold (Bimbo Jones Instrumental)\" \u2013 8:10\n* \"Hot n Cold (Bimbo Jones Radio Edit)\" \u2013 3:50\n;[[Manhattan Clique]] Mixes\n* \"Hot n Cold (Manhattan Clique Extended Club Mix)\" \u2013 4:40\n* \"Hot n Cold (Manhattan Clique Radio Edit)\" \u2013 3:54 {{col-2}}\n;[[Jason Nevins]] Mixes\n* \"Hot n Cold (Jason Nevins Club Mix)\" \u2013 7:21\n* \"Hot n Cold (Jason Nevins Radio Edit)\" \u2013 3:57\n;[[Dr. Luke]] Mix\n* \"Hot n Cold (Rock Mix)\" \u2013 3:41\n;[[Innerpartysystem]] Mix\n* \"Hot n Cold (Innerpartysystem Remix)\" \u2013 4:40\n;[[Marsheaux]] Mix<ref>https://www.discogs.com/Katy-Perry-Hot-N-Cold/release/1858395</ref>\n* \"Hot n Cold (Marsheaux Remix)\" \u2013 4:23\n;[[Yelle]] Mix\n* \"Hot n Cold (Yelle Remix)\" \u2013 4:07\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Credits and personnel==\n* [[Katy Perry]] \u2013 [[Singing|vocals]], [[songwriter]]\n* [[Dr. Luke]] \u2013 [[Record producer|producer]], songwriter, [[programming (music)|programmer]], [[Bass (instrument)|bass]], [[drums]], [[guitars|guitar]]\n* [[Max Martin]] \u2013 songwriter, guitars\n* [[Benny Blanco]] \u2013 producer, programmer, drums\n* [[Steven Wolf]] \u2013 programming\n* Serban Ghenea \u2013 [[audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing]]\n* John Hanes \u2013 mix engineer\n* Emily Wright \u2013 [[audio engineering|engineer]]\n* Sam Holland \u2013 engineer\n* Nick Banns \u2013 engineer\n* Tatiana Gottwald \u2013 engineer\n* Tina Kennedy \u2013 engineer\n\nCredits adapted from ''One of the Boys'' album liner notes.<ref name=OOTBnotes />\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2008)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Australia|4|artist=Katy Perry|song=Hot n Cold}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|1|artist=Katy Perry|song=Hot n Cold}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Belgium (Flanders)|2|arti