 waived.<ref name=\":36\" />\n|-\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Minnesota|Minnesota]]\n|March 17<ref name=\":11\" />\n|10,681<ref name=\":44\">{{Cite web|url=https://restaurant.org/Downloads/PDFs/State-Statistics/minnesota.pdf|title=Minnesota restaurant industry at a glance|last=|first=|date=2019|website=restaurant.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n|275,900<ref name=\":44\" />\n|$10.7 billion<ref name=\":44\" />\n|Sales and use tax grace period instituted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hospitalityminnesota.com/|title=Home {{!}} Hospitality Minnesota|website=Hospitality Minnesot|language=en|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Carolina|South Carolina]]\n|March 18<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wspa.com/news/gov-mcmaster-health-officials-to-hold-briefing-on-states-response-to-covid-19-at-4pm/|title=SC Gov. closes dine-in at restaurants & bars, state reports 14 new virus cases|date=2020-03-17|website=WSPA 7News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n|9669<ref name=\":46\">{{Cite web|url=https://restaurant.org/Downloads/PDFs/State-Statistics/southcarolina.pdf|title=South Carolina restaurant industry at a glance|last=|first=|date=2019|website=restaurant.org|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n|234,200<ref name=\":46\" />\n|$10.7 billion<ref name=\":46\" />\n|\n|-\n|Los Angeles\n|March 16\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Delaware|Delaware]]\n|March 18<ref name=\":15\" />\n|19,000<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.delawarerestaurant.org/about-us/|title=About Us {{!}} Delaware Restaurant Association|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-22}}</ref>\n|50,000<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.delawarepublic.org/post/coronavirus-delaware-fallout-closing-restaurants-and-bars|title=Coronavirus in Delaware: Fallout from closing restaurants and bars|last=Ciolino|first=Nick|website=delawarepublic.org|language=en|access-date=2020-